Reshape estimations with Bayesian posterior draws to long format

Source: R/reshape_draws.R
reshape_draws.Rd

Reshape a wide data.frame of posterior draws (or iterations) as columns to long format.

reshape_draws(draws, prefix = c("Draw_", "draw_", "iter_"))

Arguments

draws

data.frame containing posterior draws obtained from estimate_response or estimate_link.
prefix

The prefix of the draws (for instance, "iter_" for columns named as iter_1, iter_2, iter_3). Case sensitive. If more than one are provided, will search for the first one that matches.

Value

Data frame of reshaped draws in long format.

Examples

# \donttest{
if (require("rstanarm")) {
  model <- stan_glm(mpg ~ am, data = mtcars, refresh = 0)
  draws <- as.data.frame(insight::get_predicted(model))
  reshape_draws(draws)
}
